HEADWORD: Dousing-chock
<hw>Dous"ing-chock`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Shipbuilding)</fld> <def>One of several pieces fayed across the
apron and lapped in the knightheads, or inside planking above the upper
deck.</def> <rj><au>Ham. Nav. Encyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

